          <div class="content-text-holder" id="whatIsComputer">

            <div>

              <h1 class="t-header text">
                What is a computer?
              </h1>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text">
                A Computer is an electronic device that stores, retrieves and
                processes data. Usage: We use computers to type documents, send
                email,play games, watch movies and browse the web.Computer use
                a combination of hardware and software.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <%= image_tag("cf/ct.jpg" ,width:"500px") %>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="content-text-holder" id="oi">

            <div>

              <h1 class="t-header text">
                Input & Output Devices
              </h1>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text">Input - It is the process of entering data and programs in the
                computer system.
                <br>
                Output - Any information processed by and sent out from a
                computer or other electronic device is considered output
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <%= image_tag("cf/oi.png" ,width:"500px") %>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="content-text-holder" id="computer_components">

            <div>

              <h1 class="t-header text">
                Computer Components
              </h1>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text">
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <h3 class="text">
                      CPU
                    </h3><br>
                    <p class="text">
                      The Central Process Unit or CPU is the main microchip in
                      the computer.This distributes tasks to all other parts of
                      the computer
                    </p>
                  </li>
                  <br>
                  <li>
                    <h3 class="text">
                      Memory
                    </h3><br>
                    <p class="text">
                      RAM(Random Access Memory) is commonly called memory, and
                      stores computer code that needs to be operated on
                      quickly.This allows information held in a computer to
                      quickly interact with the CPU.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text">
                      ROM(Read Only Memory) is a type of electronic storage
                      that comes built into a device during manufacturing.
                      You'll find ROM chips in computers and many other types
                      of electronic products
                    </p>
                  </li>
                  <br>
                  <li>
                    <h3 class="text">
                      Hard Disk / Hard Drive
                    </h3><br>
                    <p class="text">
                      Hard drive is the main storage of the computer.It usually
                      stores the data permanently until it is erased.Size of
                      the hard disk is usually determined in Gigabytes.
                    </p>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <%= image_tag("cf/rr.png" ,width:"500px") %>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="content-text-holder" id="software">

            <div>

              <h1 class="t-header text">
                Software
              </h1>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text">
                Software is needed to carry out the instructions that are
                stored in the computer hardware. A collection of instructions
                that enable the user to interact with a computer, its hardware,
                or perform tasks.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <%= image_tag("cf/ss.webp" ,width:"500px") %>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="content-text-holder" id="hardware">

            <div>

              <h1 class="t-header text">
                Hardware
              </h1>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text">
                Computer hardware includes the physical parts or components of
                the computer, such as a monitor, keyboard, mouse, motherboard,
                etc. We need software for the instructions that can be stored
                and run by the hardware.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <%= image_tag("cf/hd.jpg" ,width:"500px") %>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>

            <div class="content-text-holder" id="internet">

              <div>

                <h1 class="t-header text">
                  Internet
                </h1>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text">
                  Interconnected networks which connect computers, laptops,
                  tablets, mobile phones, and televisions worldwide.
                </p>

                <p class="text">
                  Connection can be established through wired or wireless using
                  cable or modem.</p>
                <p class="text">
                  It uses the standard Internet Protocol (TCP/IP). Every
                  computer on the Internet is identified by a unique IP
                  address. IP Address is a unique set of numbers (such as
                  110.22.33.114) which identifies a computerâ€™s location.</p>

                <p class="text">
                  A special computer DNS (Domain Name Server) is used to
                  provide a name to the IP Address so that the user can locate
                  a computer by a name. For example, a DNS server will resolve
                  a name to a particular IP address to uniquely identify the
                  computer on which this website is hosted.
                </p>

              </div>

              <div>
                <%= image_tag("cf/int.png" ,width:"500px") %>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="content-text-holder" id="intranet">

              <div>

                <h1 class="t-header text">
                  Intranet
                </h1>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text">
                  Intranet is the system in which multiple PCs (Personal
                  Computers) are connected to each other.
                </p>
                <p class="text">
                  PCs on the intranet are not available to the world outside
                  the intranet.
                </p>

                <p class="text">
                  Usually each organization has its own Intranet network and
                  members/employees of that organization can access the
                  computers in their network.
                </p>
                <p class="text">
                  The Internet is not as safe as the Intranet. Intranet can be
                  safely privatized as per the need of the organization.
                </p>
                <p class="text">
                  Intranet uses internet protocols such as TCP/IP and FTP.
                </p>

              </div>

              <div>
                <%= image_tag("cf/inta.jpg" ,width:"500px") %>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="content-text-holder" id="website">

              <div>

                <h1 class="t-header text">
                  Websites
                </h1>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text t-s-header ">
                  How do websites work ?
                </p>

                <p class="text">A website is simply a collection of web pages of codes â€“
                  codes that describes the layout, format and content on a
                  page.
                </p>
                <p class="text">
                  The web server is a internet-connected computer that receives
                  the request for a web page sent by your browser.
                </p>
                <p class="text">
                  The browser connects your computer to the server through an
                  IP address. The IP address is obtained by translating the
                  domain name. Example : Chrome, Safari, IE
                </p>
                <p class="text t-s-header">
                  Why need a website ?
                </p>

                <p class="text">We need a website because in applications we may face
                  crashing of apps but in websites we will not face crashing
                  until there is a server-down. Rather than calling and getting
                  details, users can go to the website and get the information
                  they require.
                </p>
                <p class="text">Having a website is an opportunity to make a great first
                  impression and give people comfort that you're a real
                  business.
                </p>
                <p class="text">Web applications are independent of the OS.</p>
                <p class="text">
                  You can easily access the application seamlessly if you have
                  a proper Internet connection. No need for installation.
                </p>

                <p class="text">Reduces computer memory space as the files are stored on
                  cloud.
                </p>
                <p class="text">Responsive websites are also easier to maintain than apps
                  because a mobile website is accessible across platforms and
                  can be easily shared among users, as well as search engines,
                  it has far greater reach capability than a native app
                </p>
                <p class="text">If there is any issues in offline, then users can look
                  through the website
                </p>
                <p class="text">
                  Eg : You can move your business to another location without
                  affecting your sales as customers still can find you through
                  your website
                </p>
                <p class="text">Web application needs to be updated manually, web application
                  automatically updates as the cloud data is changed</p>

              </div>

              <div>
                <%= image_tag("cf/web.webp" ,width:"500px") %>
              </div>
            </div>

